data.chText: （尤指缝制或陈列服装用的）人体模型
data.enText: a model of a person, used especially when making clothes or for showing them in a shop window
a thing that seems to be real but is only a copy of the real thing

data.chText: 别在那儿干站着，你这个蠢货。
data.enText: Don't just stand there, you dummy.
an occasion when you pretend to pass the ball to another player and then do not do so
a specially shaped rubber or plastic object for a baby to suck
the cards which are placed facing upwards on the table and which can be seen by all the players
made to look real, although it is actually a copy which does not work

means: (尤指缝制或陈列服装用的)人体模型

tr: a cartridge containing an explosive charge but no bullet
a figure representing the human form
a person who does not talk

example: dummy up the books that are to be published

tr: having the appearance of being real but lacking capacity to function

value.def: A dummy is a model of a person, often used to display clothes.

example.ex: ...the bottom half of a shop-window dummy.
example.tran: 商店橱窗里假人模特的下半身

value.tran: 人体模型,假人(常用于陈列服装)

value.def: You can use dummy to refer to things that are not real, but have been made to look or behave as if they are real.

example.ex: Dummy patrol cars will be set up beside motorways to frighten speeding motorists...
example.tran: 高速公路旁将安装仿真巡逻车以威慑那些超速驾车者。

example.ex: They asked her to put together a dummy for a new magazine...
example.tran: 他们让她为一本新杂志攒一份小样。

example.ex: Soldiers were still using dummy weapons because real guns were not yet available.
example.tran: 士兵们还在用仿制的武器，因为还搞不到真家伙。

value.def: A baby's dummy is a rubber or plastic object that you give the baby to suck so that he or she feels comforted.
value.tran: (婴儿用的)橡皮奶嘴,橡皮奶头

value.boxr_value: in AM, usually use 美国英语通常用 pacifier

value.def: If you call someone a dummy, you mean that you think they are stupid.
A dummy or dummy hand is a hand of cards in a card game such as bridge or whist which is placed on the table so all the players can see it.

trans: 引锭杆；模底口用的拉杆
